<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-485-305  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 485 305.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  Oct 1 1990 v36 n1829 p20(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>IBM expands support for OSI for data com. (the OSI/Communicationssubsystem software for OS/2 Extended Edition version 1.2) (productannouncement)andM;</TITLE><TEXT><ABSTRACT>IBM introduces the OSI/Communications subsystem base OSI softwareintended to run with OS/2 Extended Edition version 1.2 and to letOS/2-based systems communicate with each other over X.25, ISO8802/3 and 8802/5 networks.andP;  The software is expected to beavailable in Mar 1991 for a one-time charge of $750; it requiresat least 7Mbytes of main memory.andP;  Also introduced is the OSI FileServices/2 package, also running under OS/2 Extended Edition andintended to provide file transfer and management between IBM andnon-IBM systems without host intervention under the ISO FTAMstandard; it is expected to be available in Jun 1991 and costs$650.andP;  IBM plans to add OSI support to OS/2 for its AS/400 seriesin the 3rd qtr of 1991.andP;  The new software packages comply with theGovernment OSI Profile (GOSIP); IBM will also provide enhanced OSIsupport for its MVS and VM mainframe operating systems.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   International Business Machines Corp. (product introduction).andO;Ticker:    IBM.andO;Product:   OSI Communications (Computer network software) (productintroduction)OSI File Services/2 (Communications software) (productintroduction).andO;Topic:     OS-2OSI StandardEnhancementsProduct IntroductionOpen Systems Interconnection StandardCommunications software.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   IBM's OSI/Communications subsystem for OS/2 Extended Edition.andO;(chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>